imes New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Post Office L</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">imited </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">is</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> pleased to respond to the</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Business, Innovation and Skills Select</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> Committee’s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> call for evidence for their short</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> inquiry into </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the Government’s proposals for the privatisation of Royal Mail.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.17pt; padding-left:3.83pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">The Post Office and Royal Mail</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">2.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The Post Office and Royal Mail are now separate businesses</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> The </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">conditions in which The Post Office operates were defined in the Postal Services Act 2011 which was in turn based upon the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">independent </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Hooper Review.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">2.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The Act</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">which included the separation of Post Office and Royal Mail also ensures that Post Office Limited remains in public ownership </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">but </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">paves the way for possible future mutualisation of the Post Office. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.17pt; padding-left:3.83pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">Government Policy position </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">3.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The Government policy posi</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">tion for the Post Office to 2015 w</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">as </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">outlined in the Department of Business, Innovation and Skills policy document</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">Securing The Post Office Network in the Digital Age</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, published in November 2010. The document stated the Government’s aims for The Post Offi</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ce</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, which included that The Post Office is not for sale, there will be no programme of closures, while there will be funding of £1.34 billion </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">to maintain and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">modernis</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">e </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the network</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">3.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The Government policy stated that there would be a minimum nationwide netw</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ork of 11,500 post offices and that the network would meet the national and l</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ocal Government access criteria.</span><a name="_ftnref1"></a><a href="#_ftn1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.17pt; padding-left:3.83pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">What separation and privatisation mean for The Post Office</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">4.1 </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Prior to the</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> separation of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Post Office and Royal Mail </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">an</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> historic long term</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> commercial agreement between</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Post Office and Royal Mail</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> was signed</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ensur</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ing </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">that </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">a strong link remains between Royal Mail Group and the Post Office to continue to supply Royal Mail products and services through its network.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">At the s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ame time separation has </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">also </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">enabled Post Office Limited to focus more on its wider business priorities such as the growth of financial services</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> including mortgages and the launch of the post office current account.   </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">4.2 </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Post Office Limited</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and Royal Mail are committed to the relationship with Royal Mail chief executive Moya Greene describing </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The Post Office as </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">‘the best and strongest network in the country, by any yardstick</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">’</span><a name="_ftnref2"></a><a href="#_ftn2">[2]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> This was reaffirmed in 2011 when she said </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">‘There is already a ve</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ry strong and enduring commercial relationship between the Post Office and Royal Mail. It is clearly in the interests of us all that this strong relationshi</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">p is maintained in the future</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">’</span><a name="_ftnref3"></a><a href="#_ftn3">[3]</a></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">4.3 </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">T</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">he Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, Dr</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> Vince Cable MP</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, has confirmed that while the two companies are separate, The Post Office and Royal Mail will work together on a commercial basis.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">‘</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The Post Office and Royal Mail will continue to work closely together. Each company needs the other. Post o</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ffices carried out over 3 billion mail transactions for Royal Mail last year. The two companies are closely linked in the public mind, and are bound together by an overwhelming commercial imperative. There is currently a long-term contract in place between</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> the two companies, and there will continue to be a long-term commercial contract in place. The chief executive of Royal Mail has said that it would </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">be “unthinkable”</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> that there will not always be a strong relationship between the Post Office and Royal Mail</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">’</span><a name="_ftnref4"></a><a href="#_ftn4">[4]</a></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">4.4 </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The Post Office is clear that </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">m</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ails services remain a very important part of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">our business</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Paula Vennells, Post Office Limited,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> Chief Executive says</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> ‘</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">we are absolutely committed to our relationship with Royal Mail</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> which is demonstrated by the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">10</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> year agreement</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> that we have in place</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">’</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Indeed we have been working closely with Royal Mail to develop new products including UK’s largest ‘click and collect’ network</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, which will ensure that both businesses are well placed to benefit from the rapidly growi</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ng parcels market, which is at the centre of Royal Mail’s growth strategy</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span><a name="_ftnref5"></a><a href="#_ftn5">[5]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.17pt; padding-left:3.83pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">Conclusion</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">5.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The Government’s </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">actions </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">to strengthen Royal Mail’s future and enable access to private capital are designed to assist Royal Mail in maintaining and developing its market and services. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">5.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The background context for Post Office Limited includes – </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">T</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">he provisions of the 2011 Postal </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Services Act</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">T</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">he long-term commercial contract established between </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Royal Mail and Post Office Limited</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">T</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">he commitments given </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">for continued close working between the companies </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">T</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">he Government’s stated policy and funding position towards the Post Office and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">i</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ts</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> network.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 17.85pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">5.3 </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The provision of mails services on behalf of Royal Mail is a key element of the Post Office business and the conditions are in place to ensure that this remains the case. It is important to Post Office Limited to have a strong Royal Mail as that can only a</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ssist our business and support </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the nationwide network of Post Office branches. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div><hr style="width:33%; height:1px; text-align:left" /><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn1"></a><a href="#_ftnref1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt"> BIS, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt; font-style:italic">Securing The Post Office Network in the Digital Age</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt">, November 2010, p. 3-6, </span><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/31809/10-1260-securing-the-post-office-network.pdf"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt; text-decoration:underline">link</span></a></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn2"></a><a href="#_ftnref2">[2]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt; font-style:italic">Hansard</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt">, Postal Services Public Bill Co</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt">mmittee, 9 November 2010, col. 18, </span><a href="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm201011/cmpublic/postalserv/101109/am/101109s01.htm"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt; text-decoration:underline">link</span></a></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn3"></a><a 